{{For|the uniform field theory of physics|Unified field theory}}

'''Uniform field theory''' is a formula for determining the effective [[electrical resistance]] of a parallel wire system. By calculating the mean square field acting throughout a section of coil, formulae are obtained for the effective resistances of single- and multi-layer solenoidal coils of either solid or stranded wire.<ref>E. F. Armstrong and T. P. Hilditch, [http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v107/n2696/abs/107573b0.html A study of catalytic actions at solid surfaces], ''Nature,''  107, pages 573-575 (30 June 1921).</ref>

